{
  "doc_id": "24508",
  "text": "2-Thiouracil and 4-thiouracil have found medical applications as anticancer and antithyroid drugs [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . Also 6-methyl-2-thiouracil exhibits antithyroid activity [CITATION_3] . But these compounds, like other nucleobases, can exist in many tautomeric forms, which may cause base-pairing mismatch leading to mutation during DNA duplication [CITATION_4] .",
